The paper deals with load balancing problems in scientific computing applications, which typically involve graph partitioning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper considers bounded-degree graphs and separator theorems, which are common topics in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of weights and costs on vertices and edges also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents an algorithm for computing the partition, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
